    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6 and boil half a kettle</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indonesian-style-pork-and-pepper-rendang-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Crush your <strong>cardamom pods</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife and discard the <strong>outer green pod[s]</strong></p><p>Grind the<strong> cardamom seeds</strong>, 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>black pepper</strong> (freshly ground is best!), <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>in a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> to form a coarse paste \u2013 this is your <strong>spice paste</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indonesian-style-pork-and-pepper-rendang-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and chop your <strong>brown onion[s] </strong>into wedges</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into strips</p><p>Add your<strong> diced pork</strong>, <strong>chipotle paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>spice paste</strong> to a bowl and mix thoroughly \u2013 this is your <strong>coated pork</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indonesian-style-pork-and-pepper-rendang-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based, <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat (Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil)</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated</strong> <strong>pork </strong>and cook for 2 min or until nicely browned</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indonesian-style-pork-and-pepper-rendang-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pork is cooking, chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the<strong> chopped creamed coconut</strong> in 200ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, then add your <strong>fish sauce</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indonesian-style-pork-and-pepper-rendang-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>onion wedges </strong>to the dish and cook for 2 min further or until slightly softened</p><p>Add the <strong>coconut stock </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and season with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indonesian-style-pork-and-pepper-rendang-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cover with the lid and put the dish in the oven for 45 min</p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p><p>After 45 min, remove the dish from the oven and add the<strong> pepper strips</strong></p><p>Return the dish to the oven, uncovered, for 15 min further or until the sauce is thickened and the pork is tender \u2013 this is your <strong>Indonesian-style pork & pepper rendang</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indonesian-style-pork-and-pepper-rendang-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Indonesian-style pork & pepper rendang </strong>over the<strong> basmati rice</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
